cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object segmentation in images. The use of a generative model and adversarial training suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The perturbation of the generative model to force it to learn object representations may also suggest a potential connection to graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the use of an autoencoder and encoder-decoder architecture may suggest a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
